 {"id": "franken_networkx-turan5", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] turan_graph produces different node labels than networkx", "description": "fnx.turan_graph(n, r) produces the complete r-partite graph with different partition node assignment than nx. Both are isomorphic (same graph class), but specific edges differ (e.g., for (5,2) nx has (0,2) but fnx has (0,1)). User code comparing specific edges diverges. Fix: rewrite Python wrapper to match nx turan_graph node partition order.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: turan_graph Python wrapper matches nx partition ordering"}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-anftup", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] add_nodes_from treats hashable 2-tuples as (node, attrs) and silently drops the 2nd element", "description": "fnx.Graph().add_nodes_from([(0,1),(0,2),(1,2)]) adds nodes [0,1] instead of the three tuple nodes. The Rust-level add_nodes_from unconditionally unpacks 2-tuples as (node, attrs) even when the tuple is hashable (second element not a dict). nx dispatches via hashability: hashable tuple -> node label; unhashable (dict in 2nd slot) -> (node, attrs). Breaks drop-in for any code that uses tuple-labeled nodes via add_nodes_from \u2014 grid_2d_graph / kneser_graph / hypercube_graph / geometric graphs all hit this. 3-tuples and longer are unaffected because Rust only special-cases length-2. Fix: Python-level wrapper on Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph matching nx hash-based dispatch.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:46:50.118934Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: add_nodes_from override matches nx hashability dispatch"}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-updatg", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] Graph.update(H) crashes when H is a Graph instance instead of edge-bunch", "description": "fnx.Graph.update (Rust-native) treats its first positional arg as an edge iterable unconditionally. nx.Graph.update duck-types: if the arg has .nodes and .edges attributes, treat it as a Graph and copy nodes+edges+graph-level attrs; otherwise treat as an edge bunch. Result: fnx.Graph().update(nx_or_fnx_Graph) raises TypeError: each edge must be a tuple (u, v) or (u, v, attr_dict). Fixed via Python-level wrapper that matches nx duck-typing. Caught via add_nodes_from adjacent-find.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:48:15.451238Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: Graph.update override duck-types Graph-like first arg"}
